Willis D. HILL v. Harold A. COX, Warden, New Mexico State Penitentiary. No. 6500. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Nov. 18, 1960. Martin G. Dumont, Denver, Colo., for appellant. F. Harlan Flint and Carl P. Dunifon, Asst. Attys. Gen., State of New Mexico, for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, LEWIS, Circuit Judge, and RICE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on ground appeal is moot.
